SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04688784
Version: 1

HPSBGN03325 rev.1 - HP SiteScope, Remote Elevation of Privilege

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2015-05-22
Last Updated: 2015-05-22

Potential Security Impact: Remote elevation of privilege

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP SiteScope. The
vulnerability could be exploited remotely to allow elevation of privilege.

References:

CVE-2015-2120 (ZDI-CAN-2567, SSRT101902)

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP SiteScope v11.1x, v11.2x, v11.3x

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2015-2120    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:S/C:C/I:P/A:C)       8.7
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

The Hewlett-Packard Company thanks 3S Labs working with HP's Zero Day
Initiative for reporting this issue to security-alert@...com.

RESOLUTION

HP has made the following updates available to resolve the vulnerability in
HP SiteScope v11.1x, v11.2x, v11.3x:

Affected version
 Resolution patch details
 Link to download

